Sentencas: A Ni/Sm0.2Ce0.8O1 (sDc) composite was employed as anode material for direct electrochemical oxidation (DEO) of dry CH4 in a solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni/SDC as anode material for dry CH4 fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The anodic performance was investigated at temperatures between 600 degrees C and 700 degrees C using SDC as electrolyte material and Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta (BSCF) as cathode material.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni/SDC as anode material for dry CH4 fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The single cell exhibited maximum power densities of 671 mW cm(-2), 494 mW cm(-2) and 305 mW cm(-2) in dry CH4 at 700 degrees C, 650 degrees C and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni/SDC as anode material for dry CH4 fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Remarkably, at 700 degrees C the power density in CH4 was higher than in H-2, thanks to the carbon tolerance of the anode.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni/SDC as anode material for dry CH4 fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Durability tests under constant 300 mA output current showed only 3.7% performance loss after 72 h operation.
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni/SDC as anode material for dry CH4 fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that Ni/SDC can be used as anode for the DEO of dry CH4 even at temperatures as low as 600 degrees C. (C) 2013
Titulo: Evaluation of Ni/SDC as anode material for dry CH4 fueled Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
